'''Robert Gonçalves Santos''' (born 28 September 1996), commonly known as '''Robert''', is a Brazilian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for free agent.

==Football career==
Born in [[São Gonçalo, Rio de Janeiro]], Robert began his career at [[Fluminense FC|Fluminense]]. He was first included in their matchday squad on 3 November 2013, remaining an unused substitute in their [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] 1–0 loss at ''[[Fla-Flu]]'' rivals [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo]]. He was called up for six more games [[2013 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|that season]], and made his debut in the final fixture on 8 December, replacing [[Kenedy (footballer)|Kenedy]] for the final 24 minutes of a 2–1 win at [[Esporte Clube Bahia]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Alves|first1=Marcus|title=Fluminense luta até o fim, vence o Bahia, mas está rebaixado para Série B|trans-title=Fluminense fight to the end, defeat Bahia, but are returning to Série B|url=http://espn.uol.com.br/noticia/375021_fluminense-luta-ate-o-fim-vence-o-bahia-mas-esta-rebaixado-para-serie-b|accessdate=24 February 2016|publisher=ESPN|date=8 December 2013|language=Portuguese}}</ref>

After only making three appearances on the bench in [[2014 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|the following year's national championship]], Robert returned for the [[2015 Campeonato Carioca]], making five appearances including his first two professional starts. On 8 February, he scored his first goal for the ''Flu''; on as a half-time substitute for [[Lucas Gomes da Silva|Lucas Gomes]], he decided a 2–1 win over [[Bangu Atlético Clube]] with five minutes remaining at the [[Maracanã Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news|title=FRED VIRA ARTILHEIRO DO NOVO MARACANÃ, ROBERT DECIDE, E FLU BATE BANGU: 2 A 1|trans-title=FRED EQUALS TOP SCORER OF THE NEW MARACANÃ, ROBERT DECIDES AND ''FLU'' BEAT BANGU 2–1|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/jogo/campeonato-carioca-2015/08-02-2015/fluminense-bangu.html|accessdate=24 February 2016|publisher=Globo|date=8 February 2015|language=Portuguese}}</ref> He scored in the [[penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] on 18 April in which his team lost 9–8 to [[Botafogo de Futebol e Regatas]] in the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jogo maluco, gol irregular, brilho de Renan: Botafogo bate Flu e vai à final|trans-title=Crazy game, strange goal, Renan's brilliance: Botafogo beat ''Flu'' and go to the final|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/rj/futebol/campeonato-carioca/jogo/18-04-2015/botafogo-fluminense/|accessdate=24 February 2016|publisher=Globo|date=18 April 2015|language=Portuguese}}</ref> Robert went on to make four substitute appearances in the [[2015 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|subsequent national league]], scoring his first goal in the tournament on 4 October, an added-time consolation in a 3–1 loss at [[Santos FC|Santos]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Santos faz dois gols em dez minutos, bate Flu por 3 a 1 e volta ao G-4 depois de cinco anos|trans-title=Santos score two goals in ten minutes, beat Fluminense 3–1 and return to G-4 after five years|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/sp/santos-e-regiao/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/04-10-2015/santos-fluminense/|accessdate=24 February 2016|publisher=Globo|date=4 October 2015|language=Portuguese}}</ref>

On 30 December 2015, Spanish [[Treble (association football)|treble]] champions [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] announced the signing of Robert, assigning him to [[FC Barcelona B|Barcelona B]] in the [[Segunda División B]] for the remainder of [[2015–16 Segunda División B|the campaign]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Barcelona sign young midfielder Robert Goncalves from Fluminense|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11833/10114647/barcelona-sign-young-midfielder-robert-goncalves-from-fluminense|accessdate=24 February 2016|agency=AFP|publisher=Sky Sports|date=30 December 2015}}</ref>

On 17 October 2018, Hong Kong club [[Kitchee SC|Kitchee]] confirmed that they would sign Robert following a successful trial in the summer.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gao |first1=Si Kei |title=華杜斯回歸傑志　施素高離隊回國照顧病父 |url=https://www.hk01.com/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E9%AB%94%E8%82%B2/247977/%E6%B8%AF%E8%B6%85%E8%81%AF-%E8%8F%AF%E6%9D%9C%E6%96%AF%E5%9B%9E%E6%AD%B8%E5%82%91%E5%BF%97-%E6%96%BD%E7%B4%A0%E9%AB%98%E9%9B%A2%E9%9A%8A%E5%9B%9E%E5%9C%8B%E7%85%A7%E9%A1%A7%E7%97%85%E7%88%B6 |website=HK 01 |accessdate=17 October 2018}} {{zh-hk icon}}</ref> On 16 January 2019, he was loaned to [[Hoi King SA|Hoi King]] in order to gain more playing time.<ref>{{cite web |title=傑志一日簽三將　羅拔被借予凱景 |url=https://hk.sports.appledaily.com/sports/realtime/article/20190116/59150921 |website=Apple Daily |accessdate=16 January 2019}} {{zh-hk icon}}</ref>

